The paper deals with the problem of estimating a random variable under privacy constraints, which is a topic that falls under the intersection of information theory (cs.IT) and cryptography (cs.CR). The paper also involves analyzing the tradeoff between privacy and utility, which is a common theme in machine learning (cs.LG) and data science (cs.DS). Additionally, the paper discusses the estimation of continuous random variables using Gaussian perturbations, which is a technique commonly used in multimedia processing (cs.MM).
